---
// DAY-166. The trust strip — four facts, no marketing fluff.
//
// Each bullet corresponds to a specific claim the product actually
// backs up in code, referenced in docs/privacy-security.md:
//
//   - Local-first      → the SQLite store lives under the user's
//                         home dir; see docs/privacy-security.md §1.
//   - No account       → there is literally no login screen, the
//                         app never talks to a Dayseam server.
//   - Keychain tokens  → crates/dayseam-secrets keys PATs by
//                         `service::account`; never on disk.
//   - No telemetry     → the desktop CSP denies any host not named
//                         in the user's own source configs.
//
// If any of these four stop being true, this file is where a
// marketing-facing regression becomes visible — the canonical
// disclosure page is docs/privacy-security.md, which must be kept
// in sync.
---

<section
  id="trust"
  class="border-y border-white/5 bg-charcoal-900/60 py-16"
  aria-label="Privacy and trust principles"
>
  <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl grid-cols-2 gap-6 px-6 md:grid-cols-4">
    <div>
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-strand-gold">
        Local first
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-300">
        Every byte of your evidence stays in a SQLite file on your laptop
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-strand-teal">
        No account
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-300">
        There is no Dayseam server. The app never phones home
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-strand-coral">
        Keychain tokens
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-300">
        GitHub / GitLab / Jira / Confluence PATs live in your macOS Keychain,
        never in plaintext on disk
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-strand-sage">
        Zero telemetry
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-300">
        Dayseam only makes outbound requests to the hosts you configure.
        Enforced by the desktop CSP
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
